{"name": "aa-student", "metadata": {"name": "aa-student", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django", "Framework :: Django :: 4.0", "Framework :: Django :: 4.2", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP", "Topic :: Internet :: WWW/HTTP :: Dynamic Content"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": "https://github.com/EVE-University/aa-student", "dependencies": ["allianceauth"], "summary": "aa-student plugin app for Alliance Auth.", "upload_time": 1735615447}, "documentation": ["\n# **EVE Uni Student Plugin for Alliance Auth**\n\nThis is a plugin app for Alliance Auth designed to assist with managing member student titles within EVE University.\n\n---\n\n## **Features**\n- Automatically manages student titles based on configurable eligibility criteria.\n- Periodically cleans up old member entries using Celery.\n\n---\n\n## **Installation**\n\n1. **Add the app to your `INSTALLED_APPS`:**\n   Add the `student` app to the `INSTALLED_APPS` section in your `settings.py` file:\n   ```python\n   INSTALLED_APPS += [\n       'student',\n   ]\n   ```\n\n2. **Apply migrations and collect static files:**\n   Run the following commands in your terminal:\n   ```bash\n   python manage.py migrate\n   python manage.py collectstatic\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## **Configuration**\n\n### **Student Eligibility Days**\nSet the number of days a member must wait before being eligible for the student title. Add the following to your `settings.py`:\n```python\nSTUDENTDAYS = 14\n```\nBy default, this is set to **14 days**.\n\n\nSet the number of people visible in the student page. Add the following to your `settings.py`:\n```python\nSTUDENTLIMIT = 50\n```\nBy default, this is set to **50 people**.\n\n\n---\n\n## **Celery Integration**\n\n### **Schedule Automatic Cleanup**\nTo enable periodic cleanup of ineligible members, add the following task to your Celery schedule in `settings.py`:\n```python\nfrom celery.schedules import crontab\n\nCELERYBEAT_SCHEDULE[\"delete_excluded_members\"] = {\n    \"task\": \"student.tasks.delete_excluded_members\",\n    \"schedule\": crontab(minute=0, hour=0),  # Runs daily at midnight\n}\n```\n\nEnsure your Celery worker and beat services are running.\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "student.migrations", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "student.migrations.0001_initial", "documentation": ["Generated by Django 4.2.17 on 2024-12-31 00:58"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "student.migrations.0001_initial.Migration", "bases": ["migrations.Migration"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "student.migrations.0001_initial.Migration.initial", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "student.migrations.0001_initial.Migration.dependencies", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "student.migrations.0001_initial.Migration.operations", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "student.views", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "student.views.index", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["List all NewMembers ordered by creation date."]}, {"name": "student.views.apply_title", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "request", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "member_id", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Apply the student title to the selected member."]}, {"name": "student.views.undo_title", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "request", "type": null